1 c. "Qualifying child" means a student who is a dependent of the taxpayer, received
2 home education under chapter 15.1 - 23 during the taxable year, and was under
3 the age of nineteen at the end of the taxable year.
4 4. The credit under this section may not exceed the taxpayer's liability as determined
5 under this chapter for the taxable year.
6 5. To receive the tax credit provided under this section, a taxpayer shall claim the credit
7 in the form and manner prescribed by the tax commissioner.
8 SECTION 2. A new subdivision to subsection 7 of section 57-38-30.3 of the North Dakota
9 Century Code is created and enacted as follows:
10 Home education income tax credit for qualified educational expenses under
11 section 1 of this Act .
12 SECTION 3. EFFECTIVE DATE. This Act is effective for taxable years beginning after
13 December 31, 2024.
